BUDDING Nigerian singer, Jed Otah, aka Dice in music circles has made good his promise to release a body of works, 48 Hours In The Motherland. The singer capitulates on his brief stay in Nigeria and the influence it has had on his career progression. The artist with this six-track masterpiece addresses some of life’s topics as seen from his lenses. Other tracks in the EP, which was released to the general public on Friday, January 21, 2022, include Prodigal, Kilode, Friendz , Lord Forgive Me, Woman, as well as True Colours.   UNLIMITED LA: My encounter with police during Sean…     Side chicks, major reason most men are still married –…     Bobrisky postpones housewarming over ‘aso-ebi design’…   Read Also: Spills makes a strong debut with ‘No Drama’ Born in the US, the artist, who has lived most of his life in the UK, says that the EP is inspired by his last visit to Nigeria where he had the opportunity to learn about his culture, people, and the entire music industry. Dice, who is of the Niger Delta extraction, noted that aside from his visit to the country, his love for life is another level of inspiration behind this project. - Advertisement - Speaking on the project, the artist says that the masterpiece boasts of an array of clinically delivered sounds ranging from Amapiano, Alte, and trap.